{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24,"type":"xterm-kitty"},"timestamp":1782118000,"idle_time_limit":3.0,"command":"bash /tmp/gpu-demo.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/bash"}}
[0.337977, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ BONUS — Multi-tenant GPU on bare metal (HAMi vGPU: no MIG hardware, no passthrough) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34m2 physical GPUs on srv-t7910 -> HAMi slices them with HARD VRAM + core limits ->\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;34ma tenant (inside its vCluster) and an LLM workload (Ollama) each get an isolated, capped slice.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.002264, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 1/4  The bare-metal GPUs (la GPU del fierro) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.152873, "o", "  node srv-t7910 advertises nvidia.com/gpu = 20   (Tesla P4 7680MiB + Quadro M4000 8192MiB)\r\n"]
[3.001861, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 2/4  A TENANT gets a HARD-capped slice (inside its own vCluster) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000109, "o", "\u001b[1;34mPod running INSIDE vcluster-tenant-a-dev. Its nvidia-smi sees ONLY its slice of an 8GB card:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.162522, "o", "  |   0  Quadro M4000                   Off |   00000000:03:00.0 Off |                  N/A |\r\n  | 47%   44C    P8             22W /  120W |       0MiB /   1500MiB |      0%      Default |\r\n"]
[0.000369, "o", "\u001b[1;32m  -> HAMi caps the tenant to 1500MiB. It cannot see or exceed its slice (hard isolation).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.001702, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 3/4  An LLM workload (Ollama) on its own slice + GPU ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.332543, "o", "  |   0  Quadro M4000                   Off |   00000000:03:00.0 Off |                  N/A |\r\n  | 49%   47C    P8             22W /  120W |    1731MiB /   4000MiB |      0%      Default |\r\n"]
[0.000424, "o", "\u001b[1;34mModel loaded (persisted on a PVC, served on the GPU):\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.282781, "o", "  NAME           ID              SIZE      MODIFIED       \r\n  llama3.2:3b    a80c4f17acd5    2.0 GB    22 seconds ago    \r\n  llama3.2:1b    baf6a787fdff    1.3 GB    5 minutes ago     \r\n"]
[2.010056, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 4/4  Ask the LLM (inference live on the sliced GPU) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34mPrompt: \"Write a short, funny love story between two Kubernetes pods.\"\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000024, "o", "\r\n"]
[6.996289, "o", "  In the bustling Kubernetes cluster, \"Pod\" McPodface fell head over deployment handles for \r\n  Kubernetes \"Label\" Lila, a fitting match due to their identical container tags. As they \r\n  spent more time together, their schedule was filled with \"Node\"-al chemistry, and soon they \r\n  were scheduling regular dates in the pod-like pods of adjacent containers. But just as \r\n  things were getting hot, Lila's scheduler kicked her out for being too \"restart\"-ful, \r\n  leaving Pod McPodface to wonder if their love would be a \"deployment\" or just a fleeting \r\n  \"nodal\" moment. In the end, they realized that their differences were what made their \r\n  relationship \"container-ously\" unique – and they were happy to be stuck in this pod-like \r\n  routine together.\r\n"]
[0.004948, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000058, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ Real cards -> HAMi-sliced -> hard-capped per tenant -> live LLM inference on the slice. ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[1.001796, "x", "0"]
